arch:property.oc:show_val: Dry sieve and flots. Medium unit from the fill of the space 89. Bones in this unit (eastern part of the space) are not so abundant as in similar unit in western part of the space. Goat is the only identified species, and most fragments are of O/C size. They belong to different body parts, and of different age. There are only few pieces that belonged to larger animal (deer size). Weathering is nonexistent to slight, and 10% of the bones are burnt. Few bones are gnawed, but many are digested, including most of the phalanges. There are two species of small fish remains, and rodent remains. Rodent bones are of brown (one upper incisor) and light color (one first lower molar, a vertebra and a long bone fragment) with some staining. Fragments of a bird sternum joined with those from 8432, modern breaks. They are all recorded as 8432. ID recorded. Dry sieve and 4 mm scraps recorded. Last number is 108.

arch:string.div: The unique identifier for each contextual unit, matching those used in the central Çatalhöyük excavation database and in publications. The excavation uses single-context recording.
